{"type":"message","id":"c7416c4f","parentId":"127dc4e4","timestamp":"2026-07-05T19:25:20.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me continue reading the ISAPI documentation to understand the correct endpoints for day/night mode, IR filter, and slow shutter (DSS).\n\nThe xlsx file at `D:\\SDK\\HIK SDK\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机20261205051227\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机\\ISAPI开发指南_球` is probably the ISAPI development guide for PTZ cameras. Let me try to extract it or read it.\n\nActually, I should use Python to read the xlsx file. Let me create a script to read the ISAPI documentation.\n\nBut first, let me understand what I've found so far:\n\n1. **Day/Night & IR Cut Filter**:\n   - Frontend: `apiPost('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/filter', { dayNightMode: mode })` - uses POST\n   - Backend: `@api_router.put(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/filter\", ...)` - expects PUT\n   - **This is a bug!** POST vs PUT mismatch\n\n2. **Slow Shutter (DSS)**:\n   - Frontend: `apiPut('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/slow-shutter', { dss_level: val })` - uses PUT ✓\n   - Backend: `@api_router.put(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/slow-shutter\", ...)` - uses PUT ✓\n   - XML sent: `<DSS version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"...\"><enabled>true/false</enabled><DSSLevel>*N</DSSLevel></DSS>`\n   \nLet me check the ISAPI documentation for the correct DSS endpoint format. I should read the xlsx file to see what the correct API format is.\n\nLet me create a Python script to read the xlsx file and extract the relevant information about Image/Filter and DSS endpoints.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully:\n\nFor the filter endpoint:\n- GET `/Image/channels/1` returns XML with `dayNightMode` and `irCutFilter` fields\n- PUT `/Image/channels/1` with modified XML to set these fields\n\nThe issue is:\n1. Frontend uses `apiPost` but backend expects `@api_router.put`\n2. The values returned from ISAPI might not match what frontend expects\n\nLet me check what values ISAPI returns for dayNightMode. Common values are:\n- \"day\" - daytime mode\n- \"night\" - nighttime mode  \n- \"auto\" - auto mode\n\nFor irCutFilter:\n- \"on\" - IR cut filter on\n- \"off\" - IR cut filter off\n- \"auto\" - auto mode\n\nThe frontend buttons have:\n- dayNightSwitch: `data-value=\"day\"`, `data-value=\"night\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"`\n- irCutSwitch: `data-value=\"on\"`, `data-value=\"off\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"`\n\nSo the values should match. The main issue is POST vs PUT.\n\nFor DSS, let me check the ISAPI documentation. I'll read the xlsx file using Python.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_c4635bd5cb7b451296e2ba5c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import pandas as pd; df = pd.read_excel('D:\\\\SDK\\\\HIK SDK\\\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机20261205051227\\\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机\\\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机.xlsx', sheet_name=None); print('Sheets:', list(df.keys())); [print(f'\\n=== {sheet} ==='); print(df[sheet].head(20).to_string()) for sheet in df.keys() if 'image' in sheet.lower() or 'filter' in sheet.lower() or 'dss' in sheet.lower() or 'day' in sheet.lower()]\"","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":894,"cacheRead":25207,"cacheWrite":21101,"totalTokens":47208,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783279502467,"responseId":"msg_329cf0da-440b-4850-8cb8-af8ea89e22f3"}}
