{"type":"message","id":"085c23f4","parentId":"8d4d62dd","timestamp":"2026-07-05T19:26:19.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The encoding is garbled but I can see some useful information. The xlsx files are reference documents (枚举值信息, 日志类型, 错误码). They don't contain the actual ISAPI endpoint documentation in a readable format.\n\nLet me look at the actual ISAPI development guide - there should be a PDF or HTML file. Let me check the ISAPI开发指南 directory more carefully. The main document might be in a different format.\n\nLooking at the earlier file listing:\n```\nD:\\SDK\\HIK SDK\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机20261205051227\\ISAPI开发指南_球型网络摄像机_DF球机\\ISAPI开发指南_球\n```\n\nThat file \"ISAPI开发指南_球\" seems to be the main guide but without a clear extension. Let me try to check what it is.\n\nActually, from the earlier glob output I see there's also a PDF:\n```\nD:\\SDK\\HIK SDK\\海康视频_ISAPI协议_V20240205\\HTTP协议报文规范.pdf\n```\n\nLet me look for the actual ISAPI development guide PDF in a different location, or I should look at the temp ISAPI folder:\n```\nD:\\SDK\\HIK SDK\\isapi_temp\\HIKVISION ISAPI_2.0-IPMD Service.pdf\n```\n\nActually, I think I have enough information from what I can see. Let me focus on the actual issues:\n\n**Issue 1: Day/Night Mode and IR Filter switches don't light up**\n\nLooking at the code:\n- Frontend `setDayNightMode()` uses `apiPost()` → sends HTTP POST\n- Backend uses `@api_router.put()` → expects HTTP PUT\n- **BUG: HTTP method mismatch!** POST will return 405 Method Not Allowed\n\n- Frontend `loadFilterStatus()` uses `apiGet()` → sends HTTP GET\n- Backend uses `@api_router.get()` → expects HTTP GET\n- This should work for loading...\n\nBut wait, the boss says \"没有任何一个亮起的\" - none of them light up. If the GET works, it should at least highlight the current position. Let me check if the `loadFilterStatus` is actually being called.\n\nLooking at console.html line 862:\n```javascript\nloadFilterStatus(deviceIp);\n```\n\nSo it IS being called during initialization. The question is: what does the ISAPI return for `dayNightMode`?\n\nThe ISAPI standard values for `dayNightMode` are typically:\n- `day` - 白天\n- `night` - 夜晚\n- `auto` - 自动\n\nAnd for `irCutFilter`:\n- `on` - 开\n- `off` - 关\n- `auto` - 自动\n\nThe frontend buttons have values:\n- dayNightSwitch: `data-value=\"day\"`, `data-value=\"night\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"`\n- irCutSwitch: `data-value=\"on\"`, `data-value=\"off\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"`\n\nThese should match if ISAPI returns those standard values. But if the device returns different values... hmm.\n\nWait, let me re-read the `updateSwitchHighlight` function:\n```javascript\nfunction updateSwitchHighlight(switchId, selectedValue) {\n    var switchEl = document.getElementById(switchId);\n    if (!switchEl) return;\n    var buttons = switchEl.querySelectorAll('.ts-btn');\n    buttons.forEach(function(btn) {\n        if (btn.dataset.value === selectedValue) {\n            btn.classList.add('active');\n        } else {\n            btn.classList.remove('active');\n        }\n    });\n}\n```\n\nAnd `loadFilterStatus`:\n```javascript\nfunction loadFilterStatus(deviceIp) {\n    apiGet('/api/v1/ptz/' + deviceIp + '/image/filter').then(function(r) {\n        if (r && r.success && r.data) {\n            updateSwitchHighlight('dayNightSwitch', r.data.dayNightMode);\n            updateSwitchHighlight('irCutSwitch', r.data.irCutFilter);\n        }\n    });\n}\n```\n\nIf `r.data.dayNightMode` returns something like `\"daytime\"` instead of `\"day\"`, or `\"night\"` works but `\"auto\"` is `\"Auto\"` (case-sensitive), then the highlight won't match.\n\nBut there's also the CSS issue - maybe the `.active` class styling is missing for triple-switch buttons. Let me check the CSS.\n\nActually, let me look at the CSS for `.ts-btn` and `.ts-btn.active` in the console.html file.\n\nLet me also check: does the `apiPost` vs `@api_router.put` mismatch cause the set to fail? Yes - POST to a PUT endpoint will get 405 Method Not Allowed. So switching is broken.\n\nFor the slow shutter issue:\n- Frontend `setSlowShutter()` uses `apiPut()` ✓\n- Backend uses `@api_router.put()` ✓\n- So the method is correct\n\nBut the boss says \"不管下拉菜单选什么，都一直是默认的*4慢快门\". Let me check the actual ISAPI XML being sent.\n\nThe backend constructs:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<DSS version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n  <enabled>true</enabled>\n  <DSSLevel>*4</DSSLevel>\n</DSS>\n```\n\nAnd PUT to `/Image/channels/1/DSS`.\n\nThe question is: is this the correct endpoint and XML format? Let me check the ISAPI docs.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The boss says \"不管选什么都一直是*4\". This could mean:\n1. The PUT request returns 200 but the value isn't actually changing (the device ignores the value)\n2. The PUT request is failing silently\n3. The XML format is wrong so the device defaults to *4\n\nWait, let me look at the setSlowShutter function more carefully:\n\n```javascript\nfunction setSlowShutter(val) {\n    var dev = window.connectedDevice ? window.connectedDevice.ip : null;\n    if (!dev) return;\n    apiPut('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/slow-shutter', { dss_level: val }).then(function(r) {\n```\n\nThe frontend sends `{ dss_level: val }` where `val` comes from the select dropdown. The dropdown options are populated from `deviceFunctionData.functions.slow_shutter.opt_values`.\n\nLooking at the HEARTBEAT.md:\n```\nopt_values=[*1.25,*1.5,*2,*3,*4,*6,*8]\n```\n\nSo the values would be like \"*1.25\", \"*1.5\", \"*2\", etc. And when the user selects one, `val` would be something like \"*2\".\n\nThe backend:\n```python\ndss_level = body.get(\"dss_level\", \"\")\nif dss_level == \"off\":\n    enabled = \"false\"\n    level_str = \"*1\"\nelse:\n    enabled = \"true\"\n    level_str = dss_level  # e.g. \"*2\"\n```\n\nSo it sends `<DSSLevel>*2</DSSLevel>` to the device. This seems correct.\n\nBut wait - maybe the issue is that the PUT to `/Image/channels/1/DSS` needs a different XML structure? Let me check if there's a specific format the device expects.\n\nActually, let me try another approach. Let me check the actual device response by looking at the astrohub logs or testing the API directly.\n\nLet me now focus on checking the triple-switch CSS and then the actual ISAPI documentation.\n\nLet me read the CSS section and the apiPost/apiPut function definitions.\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_4bb7080ca291408884592c10","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html\" -Pattern \"triple-switch|ts-btn|\\.active\" -Context 1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_02328df7ae044a2bba33c811","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html\" -Pattern \"function apiPost|function apiPut|function apiGet\" -Context 5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":1869,"cacheRead":47859,"cacheWrite":2808,"totalTokens":52542,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783279543859,"responseId":"msg_ce5a32bd-194a-4a26-9e20-e7a699750410"}}
