{"type":"message","id":"6df5be5f","parentId":"00c1aae2","timestamp":"2026-07-05T20:19:24.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to provide a comprehensive investigation and fix report for the issues they reported:\n\n1. The day/night mode and IR filter switches don't work - they don't light up and when pressed they freeze the system\n2. The slow shutter settings don't take effect - clicking doesn't change anything\n\nI already made changes to console.html to fix what I thought were the issues (changing apiPost to apiPut for the filter endpoints, and adding dropdown update for slow shutter), but the user is saying the issues persist.\n\nThe user is now asking me to investigate the ISAPIClient to understand the client object and why things aren't working. Let me continue the investigation.\n\nFrom what I can see:\n- The ISAPIClient class wasn't found with the search\n- The user mentioned that the switches don't light up at all, and pressing causes a freeze\n- The slow shutter also doesn't work\n\nI need to find where ISAPIClient is defined and understand how the client object works. Let me search more broadly.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user said:\n1. The switches don't light up at all - this means the CSS might be missing, or the JavaScript isn't working\n2. Pressing the buttons causes a freeze - this suggests a JavaScript error\n3. The slow shutter doesn't work - clicking doesn't change anything\n\nFor the slow shutter, I added code to update the dropdown value after a successful API call. But if the API call is failing or returning an error, the dropdown won't be updated.\n\nFor the switches, the issue might be:\n1. The CSS for `.ts-btn.active` is missing - so even if the JavaScript adds the class, there's no visual change\n2. The JavaScript might be throwing an error when the button is pressed\n3. The API call might be failing\n\nLet me search for ISAPIClient in the codebase to understand the client object better.\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_e41378e6bf7d4e018526afc2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\core\\ptz_controller.py\" -Pattern \"ISAPIClient|class.*Client\" | Select-Object LineNumber, Line"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\nThe user wants me to continue investigating the issues. Let me search for the ISAPIClient class definition to understand how it works.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_5e9f5f5fc09d4f05a4684828","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\" -Recurse -Filter \"*.py\" | Select-String -Pattern \"class ISAPIClient\" | Select-Object Path, LineNumber, Line"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":595,"cacheRead":136144,"cacheWrite":1889,"totalTokens":138634,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783282749902,"responseId":"msg_0d1747e9-cfbd-411d-95b6-b7fcd5c02316"}}
