{"type":"message","id":"f7b9ed24","parentId":"efdb3c37","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:07:42.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log file doesn't exist and the check_console_logs.py wasn't created. Let me:\n1. Find where the AstroHub logs actually are\n2. Check the backend API directly using curl/requests\n3. Look at the router.py code more carefully to understand the exact issue\n\nThe user asked a very pointed question: \"为什么运动控制可以读取到设备的信息？为什么WASM框体有设备的画面？\" - this means the device IS connected and working. The Playwright test confirmed `window.connectedDevice` has a valid device.\n\nThe issue is that `loadFilterStatus` was called but the buttons don't have the `active` class. This means either:\n1. The API call returned an error\n2. The response data didn't match the expected format\n3. There's a parsing issue with the ISAPI response\n\nLet me directly test the API endpoint to see what it returns, and also read the backend code to understand the exact issue.\n\nThe key insight from the user: \"是不是HTML data-value和ISAPI字段名对不上？是不是后端解析和ISAPI官方字段名对不上？\" - the user is asking me to verify the field names match between:\n1. HTML data-value attributes\n2. Backend parsing logic\n3. ISAPI official field names\n\nFrom the code I've seen:\n- HTML: `data-value=\"day\"`, `data-value=\"night\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"` for dayNightSwitch\n- HTML: `data-value=\"on\"`, `data-value=\"off\"`, `data-value=\"auto\"` for irCutSwitch\n- Backend GET: looks for `dayNightMode` and `irCutFilter` in XML\n- Backend PUT: sends `{ dayNightMode: mode }` or `{ irCutFilter: filter }`\n\nBut wait - the user said the ISAPI documentation uses `ircutFilter` (lowercase ircut), not `irCutFilter`! Let me check the code again.\n\nFrom the earlier Select-String output:\n```\nrouter.py:3696: if tag == \"dayNightMode\":\nrouter.py:3698: elif tag == \"irCutFilter\":\nrouter.py:3704: \"dayNightMode\": day_night,\nrouter.py:3705: \"irCutFilter\": ir_cut\n```\n\nAnd from the xlsx metadata:\n- Row 83: `image enum string ircutFilter:icr滤镜`\n\nThe ISAPI official field name is `ircutFilter` (lowercase 'ircut'), but the code uses `irCutFilter` (camelCase). This could be the mismatch!\n\nLet me verify this by reading the actual backend code and the ISAPI documentation.\n老板说得对！让我仔细对比 HTML、后端、ISAPI 三个地方的字段名：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_79a35d6ffe3043b8b52c5337","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport pandas as pd, glob, os\nbase = r'D:\\SDK\\HIK SDK'\nxlsx_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(base, '**', '*.xlsx'), recursive=True)\nfor f in xlsx_files:\n    if 'ISAPI' in f:\n        try:\n            df = pd.read_excel(f, sheet_name=0, header=None)\n            for i, row in df.iterrows():\n                text = ' '.join([str(v) for v in row.values if pd.notna(v)])\n                if 'ircut' in text.lower() or 'irCut' in text or 'ir_cut' in text or 'dayNight' in text:\n                    print(f'Row {i}: {text}')\n        except: pass\n\""}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n</think>\n\nThe user wants me to:\n1. Check the actual code and ISAPI documentation to find mismatches\n2. Look at the actual API response to see what values are returned\n\nLet me directly call the API endpoint and check what the device returns for the filter status. I need to:\n1. Use the existing device connection (192.168.5.72)\n2. Call the filter endpoint\n3. Compare the response with the HTML data-values\n4. Check the ISAPI XML structure\n\nLet me create a test script to:\n1. Call the API endpoint directly\n2. Parse the response\n3. Check if values match\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_b39708c3db344022bc39323a","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\"\"\"直接调用API检查滤镜状态\"\"\"\nimport requests\nimport json\n\n# 调用滤镜API\nurl = \"http://127.0.0.1:10280/api/v1/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/filter\"\ntry:\n    response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n    print(f\"Status: {response.status_code}\")\n    print(f\"Response: {json.dumps