{"type":"message","id":"2fb83a94","parentId":"a1078a33","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:08:05.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to run the test_filter_api.py script to see what the API actually returns.\n\nBut wait, I also found a critical issue in the xlsx file:\n- The ISAPI field name is `ircutFilter` (lowercase 'ircut'), not `irCutFilter`!\n\nThis means:\n- HTML data-value: `on/off/auto` ✓\n- Backend GET: looks for `irCutFilter` ❌ ISAPI uses `ircutFilter`\n- Backend PUT: sends `{ irCutFilter: filter }` → but the XML element is `<ircutFilter>`\n\nThis is the mismatch! The backend uses `irCutFilter` but ISAPI uses `ircutFilter`.\n\nLet me run the API test to confirm, then fix the code.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_e3fbb07bdf67462da5305406","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python test_filter_api.py 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":201,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":158328,"totalTokens":158535,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783285665493,"responseId":"msg_216b7524-647a-4a5a-ab73-deb19329650d"}}
