{"type":"message","id":"72dde4a9","parentId":"7df3bb27","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:08:31.190Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_532badb1e4034e869a765d2c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\r\n        root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\r\n        day_night = \"unknown\"\r\n        ir_cut = \"unknown\"\r\n        for elem in root.iter():\r\n            tag = elem.tag.split(\"}\")[-1] if \"}\" in elem.tag else elem.tag\r\n            if tag == \"dayNightMode\":\r\n                day_night = (elem.text or \"\").strip()\r\n            elif tag == \"irCutFilter\":\r\n                ir_cut = (elem.text or \"\").strip()\r\n\r\n        return {\r\n            \"success\": True,\r\n            \"data\": {\r\n                \"dayNightMode\": day_night,\r\n                \"irCutFilter\": ir_cut\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取滤镜设置异常: {e}\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n@api_router.put(\"/ptz/{device_id}/image/filter\", summary=\"设置滤镜与日夜模式\", tags=[\"Image\"])\r\nasync def set_filter_settings(device_id: str, body: dict) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"设置 dayNightMode 和/或 irCutFilter。\r\n\r\n    请求体:\r\n        {\"dayNightMode\": \"day|night|auto\", \"irCutFilter\": \"on|off|auto\"}\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    mgr: PTZDeviceController | None = _managers.get(\"ptz_controller\")\r\n    if not mgr:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": \"PTZDeviceController未初始化\"}\r\n\r\n    target_ip = _resolve_device_id_to_ip(mgr, device_id)\r\n    if not target_ip:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"无法解析设备标识: {device_id}\"}\r\n\r\n    ctrl, err = mgr._get_controller(target_ip)\r\n    if err:\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": err}\r\n\r\n    client = ctrl.client\r\n    day_night = body.get(\"dayNightMode\", \"\")\r\n    ir_cut = body.get(\"irCutFilter\", \"\")\r\n\r\n    # 先 GET 当前完整 XML，再修改对应字段后 PUT\r\n    try:\r\n        resp = await asyncio.to_thread(client.get, \"/Image/channels/1\")\r\n        if resp.status_code != 200:\r\n            return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"获取当前设置失败: HTTP {resp.status_code}\"}\r\n\n[640 more lines in file. Use offset=3740 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783285711190}}
{"type":"message","id":"651ca06e","parentId":"72dde4a9","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:09:00.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to check the actual ISAPI XML field names to see if they match the backend parsing. I need to:\n1. Get the actual raw XML from the ISAPI device\n2. Compare the field names in the XML with the backend parsing code\n3. Fix any mismatches\n\nLet me create a script to get the raw XML from the ISAPI device and compare it with the backend parsing code.\n\nThe backend parsing code looks for:\n- \"dayNightMode\"\n- \"irCutFilter\"\n\nBut the actual ISAPI might use different case or namespacing. Let me get the actual XML.老板，让我直接获取 ISAPI 设备的原始 XML 来对比字段名：<|tool_calls_section_begin|><|tool_call_begin|>functions.write:42<|tool_call_argument_begin|>{\"content\": \"\\\"\\\"\\\"获取 ISAPI Image/channels/1 原始 XML\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nimport requests\\nimport sys\\nsys.path.insert(0, r'D:\\\\SDK\\\\HIK SDK\\\\PythonSDK\\\\Lib')\\nfrom hcnetsdk import NET_DVR_Init, NET_DVR_Login_V40, NET_DVR_DEVICEINFO_V30, NET_DVR_USER_LOGIN_INFO, NET_DVR_DEVICEINFO_V30\\nimport ctypes\\nimport urllib3\\nurllib3.disable_warnings()\\n\\n# 设备信息\\nip = \\\"192.168.5.72\\\"\\nport = 80\\nusername = \\\"admin\\\"\\npassword = \\\"Nftw1357\\\"\\n\\n# 使用 requests 直接获取 ISAPI XML\\ntry:\\n    from requests.auth import HTTPBasicAuth\\n    url = f\\\"https://{ip}:{port}/ISAPI/Image/channels/1\\\"\\n    print(f\\\"GET {url}\\\")\\n    \\n    resp = requests.get(url, auth=HTTPBasicAuth(username, password), verify=False, timeout=10)\\n    print(f\\\"Status: {resp.status_code}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Content-Type: {resp.headers.get('Content-Type', 'N/A')}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"\\\\nRaw XML (first 500 chars):\\\")\\n    print(resp.text[:500])\\n    print(\\\"\\\\n\\\\nSearching for filter-related fields:\\\")\\n    for line in resp.text.split('\\\\n'):\\n        if any(kw in line.lower() for kw in ['daynight', 'ircut', 'day_night', 'ir_cut', 'filter']):\\n            print(f\\\"  {line.strip()}\\\")\\n    \\n    # 保存完整 XML\\n    with open(r'C:\\\\Users\\\\admin\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\dev-factory\\\\isapi_image_ch1.xml', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n        f.write(resp.text)\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nFull XML saved to isapi_image_ch1.xml\\\")\\n    \\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"Error: {e}\\\")\\n    import traceback\\n    traceback.print_exc()\\n\", \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\admin\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\dev-factory\\\\get_isapi_xml.py\"}<|tool_call_end|><|tool_calls_section_end|>","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The user wants me to:\n1. Check the ISAPI XML response from the actual device\n2. Compare the field names with the backend parsing code\n3. Fix any mismatches\n\nThe key issue is that the backend returns \"dayNightMode\": \"unknown\" and \"irCutFilter\": \"unknown\", which means the XML parsing is not finding the correct elements.\n\nLet me check if the ISAPI XML actually contains these fields or if they have different names/structures.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user is frustrated with my approach. They said:\n- \"如果ISAPI文档给了字段名，代码写的字段名不一样，那肯定是解析不出来的\"\n- \"你直接获取XML出来看看字段名，再对比后端代码，是不是对得上\"\n\nSo the user wants me to:\n1. Get the actual XML from the ISAPI device\n2. Compare with backend code\n3. Fix mismatches\n\nBut wait - I don't have access to the actual ISAPI device (192.168.5.72) from my code execution. The ISAPI client is in the backend, and I need to use the ISAPIClient from the backend to make the request.\n\nActually, the ISAPIClient is in the backend Python code. I can't just use `requests` to make a raw HTTP request to the device because:\n1. The device might require authentication\n2. The URL format might be different\n3. The backend already handles all this\n\nSo the correct approach is:\n1. Use the ISAPIClient from the backend to make the request\n2. Get the raw XML response\n3. Compare with the backend parsing code\n\nBut