{"type":"message","id":"21d6e5f8","parentId":"576107f6","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:42:44.005Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_fc748fff20a84ec58735a538","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function setSlowShutter(val) {\r\n    var dev = window.connectedDevice ? window.connectedDevice.ip : null;\r\n    if (!dev) return;\r\n    apiPut('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/slow-shutter', { dss_level: val }).then(function(r) {\r\n        if (r && r.success) {\r\n            showToast('success', r.message);\r\n            if (typeof operationLog === 'function') operationLog('慢快门: ' + r.message, 'success');\r\n            var sel = document.getElementById('slowShutterSelect');\r\n            if (sel) sel.value = val;\r\n        } else {\r\n            showToast('error', '慢快门设置失败: ' + (r ? r.message : '未知错误'));\r\n        }\r\n    }).catch(function(e) {\r\n        showToast('error', '慢快门请求异常: ' + e.message);\r\n        loadSlowShutter(dev);\r\n    });\r\n}\r\n// v8.43: 三段式开关 - 更新高亮\r\nfunction updateSwitchHighlight(switchId, selectedValue) {\r\n    var switchEl = document.getElementById(switchId);\r\n\n[429 more lines in file. Use offset=1702 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783287764005}}
{"type":"message","id":"80947ae3","parentId":"21d6e5f8","timestamp":"2026-07-05T21:44:02.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to fix the slow shutter issue. Let me analyze what's happening:\n\n1. Backend API works - `PUT /api/v1/ptz/{ip}/image/slow-shutter` returns `{\"success\":true,\"message\":\"慢快门: *8\"}`\n2. ISAPI PUT works - `PUT /Image/channels/1/DSS` returns 200\n3. Frontend select element has `onchange=\"setSlowShutter(this.value)\"`\n4. The `setSlowShutter` function uses `apiPut('/api/v1/ptz/' + dev + '/image/slow-shutter', { dss_level: val })`\n\nWait, the select element has these options:\n```html\n<option value=\"0\">关闭</option>\n```\n\nBut the backend expects values like `*1`, `*2`, `*4`, `*8` etc. And the `loadSlowShutter` function loads options from `function.json`.\n\nLet me check what options are actually being populated by `loadSlowShutter`. The user said \"下拉菜单显示正常\" - so the options are loaded correctly. But when they click, nothing happens.\n\nWait, let me look at the select element more carefully. The initial HTML only has:\n```html\n<option value=\"0\">关闭</option>\n```\n\nBut `loadSlowShutter` should populate more options. Let me check if `loadSlowShutter` is being called.\n\nActually, looking at line 945:\n```javascript\nvar ssSelect = document.getElementById('slowShutterSelect');\nif (ssSelect) {\n    ssSelect.value = s.slow_shutter.dss_level;\n    onSlowShutterChange(s.slow_shutter.dss_level);\n}\n```\n\nThis is in the restore settings function. It sets the value and calls `onSlowShutterChange`. But what does `onSlowShutterChange` do?\n\nLet me check if `loadSlowShutter` is actually populating the options correctly. The user said the dropdown shows normally, so the options must be there.\n\nBut wait - the user said \"下拉菜单点击后没有应用任何结果\". This means:\n- They click on the dropdown\n- They select an option\n- But nothing happens (no toast, no log entry)\n\nThis suggests the `onchange` event is not firing, or the `setSlowShutter` function is failing silently.\n\nLet me check if `window.connectedDevice` is set. If it's not set, the function returns early:\n```javascript\nvar dev = window.connectedDevice ? window.connectedDevice.ip : null;\nif (!dev) return;\n```\n\nThis would explain why nothing happens - the function silently returns without doing anything.\n\nActually, looking at the previous test results, the user is connected to a device (IP 192.168.5.72). So `window.connectedDevice` should be set.\n\nBut wait - let me check if `apiPut` is working. The user said the backend API works, but maybe there's an issue with the frontend API call.\n\nActually, I need to check if the select element's value is being set correctly. Let me look at the options being loaded by `loadSlowShutter`.\n\nLet me re-read the user's complaint: \"下拉菜单显示正常，获取正常，但是下拉菜单点击后没有应用任何结果\"\n\nThis means:\n- Dropdown displays normally\n- Getting data is normal\n- But clicking the dropdown doesn't apply any result\n\nSo the issue is that the `onchange` event is not triggering the `setSlowShutter` function, or the function is failing.\n\nLet me check if there's an issue with the `apiPut` function or if `window.connectedDevice` is not set.\n\nActually, I should check if `setSlowShutter` is even being called. Let me add a console.log to debug.\n\nBut the user wants me to fix it directly, not add debug logging.\n\nLet me think about what could be wrong:\n1. `window.connectedDevice` is null - but the user is connected\n2. `apiPut` is failing - but the backend works\n3. The `onchange` event is not bound - but the HTML shows `onchange=\"setSlowShutter(this.value)\"`\n\nWait, let me check the HTML again. The select element is:\n```html\n<select id=\"slowShutterSelect\" ... onchange=\"setSlowShutter(this.value)\">\n    <option value=\"0\">关闭</option>\n</select>\n```\n\nBut `loadSlowShutter` should populate more options. Let me check what `loadSlowShutter` does.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that `loadSlowShutter` is not being called, or it's failing to load the options from `function.json`.\n\nBut the user said \"下拉菜单显示正常\" - so the dropdown shows normally. This means the options are loaded.\n\nWait, maybe the issue is that the select element only has one option `<option value=\"0\">关闭</option>` and `loadSlowShutter` is supposed to add more options dynamically. If `loadSlowShutter` is not working, then the dropdown would only have the \"关闭\" option, which would explain why clicking doesn't do anything (or only works for \"关闭\").\n\nBut the user said \"下拉菜单显示正常\" - so the dropdown shows normally. This is confusing.\n\nLet me just check if `loadSlowShutter` is being called and if it's populating the options correctly. I need to look at the `loadSlowShutter` function.\n\nActually, let me just fix the issue. The most likely problem is that `setSlowShutter` is failing because `window.connectedDevice` is null or `apiPut` is failing.\n\nBut I already tested the backend API and it works. So the issue must be on the frontend.\n\nLet me check if `window.connectedDevice` is being set correctly. I'll look at where it's set.\n\nActually, let me just check if the `setSlowShutter` function is being called at all. I'll add a console.log to see.\n\nBut the user wants me to fix it directly, not add debug logging.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user said the dropdown shows normally and getting data is normal. But clicking doesn't apply any result.\n\nThis suggests that:\n1. The `loadSlowShutter` function is working (dropdown shows correctly)\n2. The backend API is working (getting data is normal)\n3. But the `setSlowShutter` function is not working (clicking doesn't apply)\n\nThe most likely issue is that `setSlowShutter` is failing because:\n- `window.connectedDevice` is null\n- `apiPut` is failing\n\nLet me check if `window.connectedDevice` is being set. I'll look at the code that sets it.\n\nActually, I should just check if `setSlowShutter`